PluginController.html.title: PluginController
PluginController.html.name: PluginController
PluginController.html.description: Class for controlling Haxball Headless Manager (HHM) plugins.

PluginController.html#getPlugin.title: <async> getPlugin( name ) → {Promise.<?PluginData>}
PluginController.html#getPlugin.name: getPlugin
PluginController.html#getPlugin.description: Returns PluginData of the given plugin name.

PluginController.html#enablePlugin.title: <async> enablePlugin( name ) → {Promise.<boolean>}
PluginController.html#enablePlugin.name: enablePlugin
PluginController.html#enablePlugin.description: Enables a HHM plugin with the given name.

PluginController.html#disablePlugin.title: <async> disablePlugin( name [, recursive ] ) → {Promise.<Array.<number>>}
PluginController.html#disablePlugin.name: disablePlugin
PluginController.html#disablePlugin.description: Disables a HHM plugin with the given name. If the name is an Array then it disables all the plugins in the given order.

PluginController.html#getPluginsThatDepe.title: <async> getPluginsThatDependOn( name [, recursive [, includeDisabled ] ] ) → {Promise.<Array.<PluginData>>}
PluginController.html#getPluginsThatDepe.name: getPluginsThatDependOn
PluginController.html#getPluginsThatDepe.description: Gets a list of plugins that depend on the given plugin.

PluginController.html#hasPlugin.title: <async> hasPlugin( name ) → {Promise.<boolean>}
PluginController.html#hasPlugin.name: hasPlugin
PluginController.html#hasPlugin.description: Checks if the room has a plugin with given name loaded.

PluginController.html#addPlugin.title: <async> addPlugin( plugin [, pluginConfig ] ) → {Promise.<number>}
PluginController.html#addPlugin.name: addPlugin
PluginController.html#addPlugin.description: Adds a new plugin. If the plugin is string, then it will be loaded from the available repositories. If the plugin is Plugin, then it will be loaded from contents of Plugin.

PluginController.html#setPluginConfig.title: <async> setPluginConfig( pluginConfig [, pluginName ] )
PluginController.html#setPluginConfig.name: setPluginConfig
PluginController.html#setPluginConfig.description: Sets the rooms plugin config. Merges the new config with the old one. Tries to load plugins that are not loaded from the available repositories and removes the loaded plugins that are not in the given config. If pluginName is given then only config for the given plugin is set.

PluginController.html#getPluginConfig.title: <async> getPluginConfig( [ pluginName ] ) → {Promise.<object>}
PluginController.html#getPluginConfig.name: getPluginConfig
PluginController.html#getPluginConfig.description: Returns the plugin config for all loaded plugins in the room or if pluginName is given, then return the config for that plugin.

PluginController.html#reloadPlugin.title: <async> reloadPlugin( pluginName [, safe ] ) → {boolean}
PluginController.html#reloadPlugin.name: reloadPlugin
PluginController.html#reloadPlugin.description: Reloads a plugin from the configured repositories. This is a wrapper around the HHM PluginManager.reloadPlugin method. See https://github.com/saviola777/haxball-headless-manager/blob/master/src/classes/PluginManager.js#L565

Haxroomie.html.title: Haxroomie
Haxroomie.html.name: Haxroomie
Haxroomie.html.description: Class for spawning the headless chrome browser and managing RoomControllers. Each RoomController controls one room running in a browsers tab. After creating the Haxroomie instance it is required to launch the browser with the launchBrowser method before anything else.

Haxroomie.html#launchBrowser.title: <async> launchBrowser()
Haxroomie.html#launchBrowser.name: launchBrowser
Haxroomie.html#launchBrowser.description: Launches the puppeteer controlled browser using the remote-debugging-port given in Haxroomie classes constructor. It is only possible to launch one browser.

Haxroomie.html#hasRoom.title: hasRoom( id ) → {boolean}
Haxroomie.html#hasRoom.name: hasRoom
Haxroomie.html#hasRoom.description: Checks if there is a room running with the given id.

Haxroomie.html#getRoom.title: getRoom( id ) → {RoomController}
Haxroomie.html#getRoom.name: getRoom
Haxroomie.html#getRoom.description: Returns a RoomController with the given id.

Haxroomie.html#getRooms.title: getRooms() → {Array.<RoomController>}
Haxroomie.html#getRooms.name: getRooms
Haxroomie.html#getRooms.description: Returns an array of available RoomControllers.

Haxroomie.html#getFirstRoom.title: getFirstRoom() → {RoomController}
Haxroomie.html#getFirstRoom.name: getFirstRoom
Haxroomie.html#getFirstRoom.description: Returns the RoomController that was first added.

Haxroomie.html#removeRoom.title: <async> removeRoom( id )
Haxroomie.html#removeRoom.name: removeRoom
Haxroomie.html#removeRoom.description: Removes a RoomController with the given id. Removing deletes the RoomController and closes the browser tab it is controlling.

Haxroomie.html#addRoom.title: <async> addRoom( roomController [, roomControllerOptions ] ) → {RoomController}
Haxroomie.html#addRoom.name: addRoom
Haxroomie.html#addRoom.description: Adds a new RoomController. If roomController is a string or number, then it will be used as an id for the new RoomController.

RepositoryController.html.title: RepositoryController
RepositoryController.html.name: RepositoryController
RepositoryController.html.description: Class for controlling Haxball Headless Manager (HHM) repositories.

RepositoryController.html#addRepository.title: <async> addRepository( repository [, append ] ) → {Promise.<boolean>}
RepositoryController.html#addRepository.name: addRepository
RepositoryController.html#addRepository.description: Adds a repository. If append is set to true, the new repository will be added with the lowest priority, i.e. plugins will only be loaded from it they can't be found in any other repository. Otherwise the repository will be added with the highest priority.

RepositoryController.html#setRepositorie.title: <async> setRepositories( repository ) → {Promise}
RepositoryController.html#setRepositorie.name: setRepositories
RepositoryController.html#setRepositorie.description: Sets the repositories. Overwrites all repositories with the given array of repositories. Adds saviolas default repository if its not defined in the given array.

RepositoryController.html#hasRepository.title: <async> hasRepository( repository ) → {boolean}
RepositoryController.html#hasRepository.name: hasRepository
RepositoryController.html#hasRepository.description: Returns whether the given repository already exists. Repositories are considered equal if their configuration is the same.

RepositoryController.html#getRepositoryI.title: <async> getRepositoryInformation( repository ) → {RepositoryData}
RepositoryController.html#getRepositoryI.name: getRepositoryInformation
RepositoryController.html#getRepositoryI.description: Retrieves information about the given repository. The information is loaded from repositorys repository.json config file.

RoomController.html.title: RoomController
RoomController.html.name: RoomController
RoomController.html.description: RoomController provides an interface to communicate with HaxBall roomObject and Haxball Headless Manager (HHM). Each RoomController controls one tab in the headless browser. You can create new RoomController instances with the Haxroomie#addRoom factory method. The API provides a Promise ready way to call the methods or optionally you can listen to the events each method fires.

RoomController.html#roomInfo.title: roomInfo :object
RoomController.html#roomInfo.name: roomInfo
RoomController.html#roomInfo.description: If room is running, contains its data (like e.g. roomInfo.roomLink). If not running, then this is null. Returns a copy of the original object.

RoomController.html#openRoomLock.title: openRoomLock :boolean
RoomController.html#openRoomLock.name: openRoomLock
RoomController.html#openRoomLock.description: If opening of the room is in process, then this will be true.

RoomController.html#plugins.title: plugins :PluginController
RoomController.html#plugins.name: plugins
RoomController.html#plugins.description: Object that can be used to control and get information about plugins. Requires the room to be running!

RoomController.html#repositories.title: repositories :RepositoryController
RoomController.html#repositories.name: repositories
RoomController.html#repositories.description: Object that can be used to control and get information about repositories. Requires the HHM library to be loaded! To load HHM you can use the init() method or open the room with openRoom().

RoomController.html#roles.title: roles :RoleController
RoomController.html#roles.name: roles
RoomController.html#roles.description: Object that can be used to control and get information about roles. Requires the room to be running and sav/roles plugin to be loaded and enabled!

RoomController.html#init.title: <async> init( [ options ] )
RoomController.html#init.name: init
RoomController.html#init.description: Initializes the RoomController by navigating the page to the headless HaxBall URL and loads the Haxball Headless Manager library. This enables the use of the repositories object to get information about repositories before opening the room. Note that calling close will undo this.

RoomController.html#openRoom.title: <async> openRoom( config ) → {object}
RoomController.html#openRoom.name: openRoom
RoomController.html#openRoom.description: Opens a HaxBall room in a browser tab. On top of the documentated properties here, the config object can contain any properties you want to use in your own HHM config file. The config object is usable globally from within the HHM config as the hrConfig object.

RoomController.html#closeRoom.title: <async> closeRoom()
RoomController.html#closeRoom.name: closeRoom
RoomController.html#closeRoom.description: Closes the headless HaxBall room by navigating the page out of the headless HaxBall URL.

RoomController.html#callRoom.title: <async> callRoom( fn ) → {Promise.<any>}
RoomController.html#callRoom.name: callRoom
RoomController.html#callRoom.description: Calls a function of the HaxBall roomObject in the browsers context.

RoomController.html#eval.title: <async> eval( pageFunction [, ...args ] ) → {Promise.<Serializable>}
RoomController.html#eval.name: eval
RoomController.html#eval.description: Wrapper for Puppeteers page.evaluate. Evaluates the given code in the browser tab this instace is controlling. You can access the HaxBall roomObject with HHM.manager.room. e.g. room.eval('HHM.manager.room.getPlayerList()');
